'''11-Eicosenoic acid''', also called '''gondoic acid''', is a [[Monounsaturated fat|monounsaturated]] [[omega-9 fatty acid|omega-9]] [[fatty acid]] found in a variety of plant oils and [[Nut (fruit)|nuts]]; in particular [[jojoba oil]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Miwa |first1=Thomas |last2= |first2= |year=1971 |title=Jojoba Oil Wax Esters and Derived Fatty Acids and Alcohols: Gas Chromatographic Analyses |journal=Journal of the American Oil Chemists Society |volume=48 |issue=6 |pages=259–264 |publisher= |doi= |url=http://naldc.nal.usda.gov/download/31317/PDF |accessdate=May 6, 2013}}</ref> It is one of a number of [[eicosenoic acid]]s.

