{{Infobox company | name = Augstsprieguma Tīkls AS | logo = Ast-logo-rgb.png | caption = | type = [[Public company|State-owned company]] | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = {{start date|1939|10|15}} | defunct = | location_city = [[Riga]] | location_country = [[Latvia]] | location = | locations = | area_served = [[Latvia]] | key_people = Varis Boks (CEO) | industry = [[Electricity]] | production = | services = [[Electric power transmission]] | revenue = €158.86&nbsp;million | operating_income = | net_income = €309,244 | assets = | equity = | owner = [[Ministry of Finance of Latvia]] | num_employees = 520 | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{url|http://www.ast.lv/en}} | footnotes = }}
'''Augstsprieguma Tīkls AS''' ('''AST''') is an independent electricity transmission system operator in [[Latvia]]. It operates power systems with voltages of 110&nbsp;kV and above, which is leased from [[Latvenergo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ast.lv/en/content/about-us|title=Abou us | publisher = Augstsprieguma Tīkls |archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-08-10}}</ref>
On 15 October 1939 the [[Ķegums Hydroelectric Power Station|Ķegums power plant]] and the first substation in [[Riga]] start operation. This day is considered as the beginning of AST.<ref name="ast"/>
AST was a part of [[Latvenergo]]. On 2 January 2012, it was unbundled from Latvenergo and the [[Ministry of Finance of Latvia]] became the sole shareholder of AST.<ref name="ast"> {{cite web | url = http://www.ast.lv/en/history | title = History | publisher = Augstsprieguma tikls | accessdate = 2013-04-05}} </ref>
In December 2017, AST bought from [[Uniper Ruhrgas International]] and Itera Latvija 18.31% and 16.05% stakes in [[Conexus Baltic Grid]], a natural gas transmission system operator in Latvia, for €57.394&nbsp;million.<ref name=leta271217> {{cite news | url = https://www.leta.lv/eng/home/important/133C9DB3-F88C-D487-A540-A891BF4CF5AC/ | title = Augstsprieguma Tikls acquires shares in Conexus Baltic Grid from Itera Latvija | agency = [[LETA]] | date = 2017-12-27 | accessdate = 2018-03-28}} </ref>
In 2017, the company had a turnover of €158.86&nbsp;million and a profit of €309,244.<ref name=delfi270718> {{cite news | url = http://www.delfi.lv/bizness/biznesa_vide/regulators-bazigs-par-augstsprieguma-tikla-speju-investet-atseviskos-infrastrukturas-objektos.d?id=50252177 | title = Regulators bažīgs par 'Augstsprieguma tīkla' spēju investēt atsevišķos infrastruktūras objektos | trans-title = The regulator is concerned about the ability of Augstsprieguma tīkl7 to invest in certain infrastructure objects | work = [[Delfi (web portal)|Delfi]] | agency = [[LETA]] | date = 2018-07-27 | accessdate = 2018-08-11}} </ref> In August 2018, the share capital of the company was increased up to €63,139,313 by converting the loan of €57.394&nbsp;million for purchasing share in Conexus Baltic Grid into the share capital.<ref name=delfi060818> {{cite news | url = http://www.delfi.lv/bizness/uznemumi/augstsprieguma-tikls-palielina-pamatkapitalu-par-57-4-miljoniem-eiro-lai-atmaksatu-aizdevumu.d?id=50279735 | title = 'Augstsprieguma tīkls' palielina pamatkapitālu par 57,4 miljoniem eiro, lai atmaksātu aizdevumu | trans-title = Augstsprieguma tīkls boosts equity capital by 57.4 million euros to repay the loan | work = [[Delfi (web portal)|Delfi]] | date = 2018-08-06 | accessdate = 2018-08-11}} </ref>
AST plans to invest €445&nbsp;million in the Latvian power transmission system in 2018-2027.<ref name=bc120917> {{cite news | url = http://www.baltic-course.com/eng/energy/?doc=133093 | title = Power transmission system's development plan for 2018–2027 approved in Latvia | work = The Baltic Course | date = 2017-09-12 | accessdate = 2018-08-11}} </ref> In 2018, it invests €89.05&nbsp;million, of which €62.1&nbsp;million will be spent on implementation of the third stage in construction of the Kurzeme Ring power transmission line and €4.25&nbsp;million in construction of the third power interconnection between Estonia and Latvia.<ref name=leta230518> {{cite news | url = https://www.energycentral.com/news/latvian-power-grid-operator-augstsprieguma-tikls-invest-eur-8905-million-development-year | title = Latvian power grid operator Augstsprieguma Tikls to invest EUR 89.05 million in development this year | work = Energy Central | agency = LETA | date = 2018-05-23 | accessdate = 2018-08-11}} </ref>
