'''Psyllic acid''' (also '''pysslostearic acid''', '''tritriacontanoic acid''' or '''ceromelissic acid''') is a [[saturated fat|saturated fatty acid]].
==Alkali salts== The alkali [[salt (chemistry)|salts]] of psyllic acid are precipitated when alcoholic solutions of the acid and an [[alkali hydroxide]] are mixed. The silver and barium salts can be obtained by adding aqueous alcoholic solutions of [[silver nitrate]] and [[barium chloride]] to alcoholic solutions of the acid. The following salts have been analyzed: C<sub>38</sub>H<sub>65</sub>O<sub>2</sub>Na, C<sub>66</sub>H<sub>130</sub>O<sub>4</sub>Ba, and C<sub>33</sub>H<sub>65</sub>O<sub>2</sub>Ag. Psylla wax is [[hydrolysis|hydrolyzed]] by alcoholic [[potassium hydroxide]] as well as by [[hydrobromic acid]].<ref name='JCS1908'>{{cite journal|title=Abstracts of Papers on Organic Chemistry|journal=Journal of the Chemical Society|year=1908|first=|last=|volume=94|issue=1|pages=123|id= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tO44AAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover |format=|accessdate=2010-05-10 }}</ref><ref name='Sundvik'>Psylla Wax. IV. Psyllic Acid and its Salts. Ernst E. Sundvik (Zeitsch. physiol. Chem., 1908, 54, 255-257. Compare Abstr., 1898, i, 617; 1901, i, 358; 190, i, 887)</ref>
==Nutritional sources== Psyllic acid is present in [[Wolfberry|Chinese wolfberries]].<ref name='crc-li'>{{cite book | last = Thomas S. C. | first = Li | authorlink = | title = Vegetables and Fruits: Nutritional and Therapeutic Values | publisher = CRC Press | year = 2008 | location = | pages = 41 | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = 978-1-4200-6871-9 }}</ref><ref name='Ram'>{{cite journal|title=Herbal Preparations as a Source of Hepatoprotective Agents|journal=Drug News & Perspectives|year=2001|first=Vishnu Ji|last=Ram|volume=14|issue=6|pages=353|id= |url=https://journals.prous.com/journals/servlet/xmlxsl/pk_journals.xml_summary_pr?p_JournalId=3&p_RefId=250&p_IsPs=Y|format=|accessdate=2010-05-10 }}</ref>
